text:
(1)
Kimball Street, east side, south from Ave. V. A view of the foot of Kimball Street, ending in Jamaica Bay. At the left, is a Boat Dock, and storage place.
February 26, 1931.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)
The same, another angle.
February 26, 1931.

P. L. Sperr.

(3)
The same, looking southeast along Kimball Street, from Ave. U and East 36th Street, showing Hemlock City in the background; now a section of Brooklyn between Floyd Bennett Field and Marine Park.
About 1931.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
